    "commitMessage": "HardwareIsolation: Added the \"CreateWithEntityPath\" interface\n\nIn an open-POWER based system, user can isolate hardware or\nthe application can isolate hardware in the error path if the\nhardware is a fault and the respective isolated hardware part\nwill be ignored to init during the next host boot.\n\nSo, this interface will be used to isolate a hardware part by\nusing a hardware entity path which is a key between BMC open-POWER\nbased applications and Host applications.\n  - It will create an org.open_power.HardwareIsolation.Entry\n    object and also create a record into pnor hardware isolation\n    partition so, that the host application can use that record\n    to isolate hardware during the next host boot.\n\nPlease refer https://gerrit.openbmc-project.xyz/c/openbmc/docs/+/27804\nto get more details of hardware isolation.\n\nSigned-off-by: Ramesh Iyyar <rameshi1@in.ibm.com>\nChange-Id: I137cbff40bcef6cef2acdad2c8f19bf9ed8bf029\n",
